commit.message: Add missing 'is'.
If an explicit name is given, use it.
rwops: Add splitfiles, fix issues with subfiles.
Fix parameters to from_buffer.

Rewrite rwobject, create a new RWopsIO class.

This is intended as a replacement for SubFile in Ren'Py, and
represents a Python file that's backed by SDL_rwops.

This avoids double-opens in more cases where Ren'Py opens
a file, and also cleans up rwobject.pyx, removing a ton
of special-case constructor functions.

Position the window, then show it.

(Newer versions of SDL seem to ignore the positioning arguments
to SDL_CreateWindow.)
Additional required changes.

commit.message: Move changes to support WINDOWMOVED event
Add the WINDOWMOVED event.
Add support for shaped windows.

Update how virtual input mode works

Between SDL1.2 and SDL2 the method for switching to relative mouse mode
changed, breaking pygame's virtual input mode. This patch is based on a
change in pygame proper from 2019 made to address this issue.

Handle SDL_DROP* events.

Fixes renpy/renpy#4615.

Do not restore a fullscreen window.

Fixes renpy/renpy#4603.

Do not disable fullscreen spaces on the mac.

Now that Ren'Py is the main pygame_sdl2 user, it's fine to assume
windows are resizeable. Disabling it also causes a crash.

Fixes renpy/renpy#4600
Integrates maximize with window resizing.
Add a way to directly load pixel data into a surface.
Add the ability to get and set the window position.

Include headers in distributions.

Fixes #75.
Store the instance_id as part of the Controller object.
Go back for using setuptools.

Add additional fields to events, matching pygame.

In a few cases, that means the same field will be available twice,
for compatibility reasons.
Use the correct compatibility macro.

commit.message:
Add name attribute to RWops when created from a file

This is needed for webaudio to work has it needs the audio file location
instead of a file object.

Allow compilation with SDL_image < 2.6

These are missing symbols for JXL, AVIF, and SVG scaling. So we
indirect the header through a compatibility header that provides
stubs of the missing functionality.

Fixes renpy/renpy-build#58.
